            </p><br/>
            <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
                Recently, many provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities have published the "report card" of economic operation in the first half of 2019. As of July 29, 25 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities have published data on major economic indicators. Among them, 14 provinces, such as Yunnan, Guizhou and Jiangxi, have a faster economic growth rate than 6.3% of GDP in the whole country; Beijing's growth rate is the same as that in the whole country; and 10 provinces, such as Chongqing and Gansu, have a slower growth rate than that in the whole country.
            </p><br/>
            <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Economic growth is in a reasonable range</p>
            <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
